overview: The user initiated a review of a recently implemented sleep
  questionnaire application. The primary goal was to ensure that the database,
  API endpoints, and overall functionality adhered to the acceptance criteria
  outlined in the Statement of Work. The application is designed as a freemium,
  interactive tool that collects de-identified demographic data (year of birth,
  zip code/county, sex) and patient responses. It aims to provide a narrative
  report, linking to educational resources and clinicians, and offering probable
  diagnoses for various sleep disorders or guidance for sleep health
  optimization. The review of the codebase confirmed the implementation of core
  features such as the interactive questionnaire form, API endpoints for
  response submission, CSV data export, PDF report generation, and an
  administrative dashboard for data access and management, including a secure
  login system.
